The comic and television series heroine will be officially designated as the UN honorary ambassador for the empowerment of women and girls during a ceremony attended by UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon on October 21.DC Entertainment President Diane Nelson will attend along with "surprise guests" - possibly actress Lynda Carter (pictured below) who portrayed Wonder Woman in the hit TV series in the 1970s.The ceremony will launch a year-long campaign on gender equality and women's empowerment, which is one of the UN's new global goals for the next 15 years.